  "datePublished": "2026-03-04",
  "description": "Observations can expose vulnerable species to harm. iNaturalist provides geoprivacy settings, but the observer must decide when to use them.\n¶Practice guidance Use obscured or private locations for threatened or collectible species. Consider local regulations and community guidance for sensitive taxa. Document the reason for geoprivacy in observation notes when possible. ¶Scientific tradeoffs Conservation value vs. risk exposure: precise data can help management but also enable harm. Spatial resolution: obscured records reduce location precision; compensate with detailed habitat notes. ¶Cultural sensitivity and access Some species and locations have cultural significance beyond conservation status. If local guidance indicates sensitivity, prioritize protection over precision.\n",
  "name": "Sensitive species and obscured locations",
